					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I find Jagasian's point persuasive. A cheap and easy-to-emulate-accurately mapper would be ideal for modern NES development. <a href="http://forum.6502.org/viewtopic.php?p=6630#6630" class="postlink">Someone on 6502.org posted</a> that the SX series microcontrollers can be had for under $3 a piece and run at 75 MHz, allowing them to emulate a programmable logic device plenty fast for a NES. These devices work on the principle that instead of having dedicated hardware, you just do almost all of it in software using a high clock rate.</div>

